	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CONCEPTS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_ALLIANCE_YIELDS_TITLE",                "Corresponding Yield of Alliance"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CONCEPTS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_ALLIANCE_YIELDS_PARA_1",               "[ICON_BULLET]Religious: +1 [ICON_FAITH] Faith[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Scientific: +1 [ICON_SCIENCE] Science[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Cultural: +1 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Economic: +3 [ICON_GOLD] Gold[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Militaristic: +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CONCEPTS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_ALLIANCE_GPP_TITLE",                   "Corresponding Great Person of Alliance"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CONCEPTS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_ALLIANCE_GPP_PARA_1",                  "[ICON_BULLET]Religious: [ICON_GreatProphet] Great Prophet[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Scientific: [ICON_GreatScientist] Great Scientist[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Cultural: [ICON_GreatWriter] Great Writer [ICON_GreatArtist] Great Artist [ICON_GreatMusician] Great Musician[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Economic: [ICON_GreatMerchant] Great Merchant[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Militaristic: [ICON_GreatGeneral] Great General [ICON_GreatAdmiral] Great Admiral"),
	-- 游戏进度相关调整
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE",                      "Game Progress Related"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_FEATURE_RESOURCE_YIELDS_TITLE",   "Yields of Removing Features and Harvesting Resources"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_FEATURE_RESOURCE_YIELDS_PARA_1",  "The instantaneous benefits of removing features and harvesting resources (commonly known as chopping) no longer increase, with the base 24 point benefit for removing features (distributed by feature type) and the base 32 point benefit for harvesting resources (distributed by resource type). See the ""Terrains and Features"" and ""Resources"" Page for details."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_FEATURE_RESOURCE_YIELDS_PARA_2",  "Luxury and strategy can be harvested or covered by wonders or Districts, after mastering the corresponding prerequisite technologies."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_PILLAGE_YIELDS_TITLE",            "Pillage Yields"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_PILLAGE_YIELDS_PARA_1",           "Remove the setting that pillage gains increase with the ""game progress"", and replace it with a fixed base of 25 points per time (yield type is determined by the pillage target)."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_DISTRICT_PROJECT_COST_TITLE",     "Cost of Districts and Projects"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_DISTRICT_PROJECT_COST_PARA_1",    "The pricing of districts has been changed to based on the number of previous copies built (denote as N), with most specialized districts priced at 75 + 15N [ICON_Production] Production, most Unique Districts priced at 60 + 12N [ICON_Production] Production, and other districts priced at a fixed value. See the ""Districts"" page for details."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_DISTRICT_PROJECT_COST_PARA_2",    "The cost of the projects corresponding to the specialized districts increase according to the ""game progress"", from 40 to 440. the output of the corresponding Great People points has been changed to (project cost / 5 + 2) * 2, halve for projects that generate multiple types of Great People points."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_GPP_TITLE",                       "Great Person Points"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_PROGRESS_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_GPP_PARA_1",                      "All content related to Great People points are doubled (i.e. 2 Great People points currently equal to 1 Great People point previously)."),
	-- 城市相关调整
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE",                               "City-related Adjustments"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_CITY_CENTER_YIELDS_TITLE",                 "Yields of City Center"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_CITY_CENTER_YIELDS_PARA_1",                "The guaranteed yields of City Center has been adjusted to +3 [ICON_FOOD] Food and +2 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_POPULATION_TITLE",                         "Population Formula"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_POPULATION_PARA_1",                        "Each [ICON_Citizen] Population consumes 3 [ICON_Food] Food. The formula for the food needed for population growth is changed to 16 + 7n + n^2.05, where ""n + 1"" is the number of population the city has."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_PLOT_PURCHASE_TITLE",                      "Purchase plots & Land Expansion"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_PLOT_PURCHASE_PARA_1",                     "The base price of purchase plots is adjusted to 40 (was 50), The range of natural land expansion through cultural influence is changed to 8 tiles (instead of 5 tiles)."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_DISTRICT_CITIZEN_TITLE",                   "Citizen"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_DISTRICT_CITIZEN_PARA_1",                  "Citizen in each Districts (specialists) now provide great People points of corresponding types (e.g., 4 Great Scientist Points for each citizen work in Campus). The District itself also provides one citizen slot. Each level of buildings increase the yields of citizen (specialists) working in the districts."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_AMENITY_TITLE",                            "Amenity"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_AMENITY_PARA_1",                           "Free Amenity of cities change back to 1 (from 0). Add a new [ICON_Amenities] Amenity status:"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_CITY_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_AMENITY_PARA_2",                           "[ICON_BULLET] Delighted (new): Requires city have +2 to +3 [ICON_Amenities] Amenities, result in 5% growth rate and 5% non-food yields.[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET] Happy: Requires city have +4 to +5 [ICON_Amenities] Amenities, result in 10% growth rate and 10% non-food yields.[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET] Joyful (new): Requires city have +6 to +7 [ICON_Amenities] Amenities, result in 15% growth rate and 15% non-food yields.[NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET] Ecstatic: Requires city to reach +8 [ICON_Amenities] Amenities, result in 20% growth rate and 20% non-food yields."),
	-- 时代相关调整
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_ERA_PAGE_CHAPTER_CONTENT_TITLE",                           "Era-related Adjustments"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_ERA_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_GAME_ERA_TURNS_TITLE",                 "Pace of the World Era Changes"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_ERA_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_GAME_ERA_TURNS_PARA_1",                "When the ""Slower pace of the world era changes"" option is not enabled, the pace of world era change is accelerated. In the ancient era, it takes a minimum of 20 turns and a maximum of 44 turns; from the classical to the industrial era, it takes a minimum of 15 turns and a maximum of 20 turns; for subsequent eras, it takes a minimum of 20 turns and a maximum of 40 turns."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_ERA_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_GAME_ERA_THRESHOLD_TITLE",             "Era Score Threshold"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_ERA_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_GAME_ERA_THRESHOLD_PARA_1",            "Adjust the calculation of the era score threshold: [NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET] Each time you enter the Golden Age, the era score requirement increases by 10 points (was 5). The requirement for era score decreases by 10 points (was 5) each time you enter the Dark Age. [NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET] The era score requirement increases by 2 points (was 1) for every city you own."),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_ERA_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_ERA_SCORE_TITLE",                      "Gain Gold from Era Score"),
	("LOC_PEDIA_CONCEPTS_PAGE_HD_GAME_ERA_PAGE_CHAPTER_HD_ERA_SCORE_PARA_1",                     "New mechanism: Gains 5 [ICON_Gold] Gold for every era score earned. If one loses their era points through certain means, the corresponding amount of [ICON_GOLD] gold coins will also be deducted."),

